  "body": "Hey. The only way i found how to unmount component in tests is \n\n``` js\nunmount: function(component) {\n    if (component && component.isMounted()) {\n        React.unmountComponentAtNode(component.getDOMNode().parentNode);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWhen i render component with `ReactTestUtils.renderIntoDocument(...)` and return `null` from `render` method, `getDOMNode()` also returns `null`, and i'm not able to unmount component. Is there any workarounds?\n\nP.S. Talking about 0.13\n",
